case_address_found_1: 30 miles of off Gulf of Mexico
case_circumstances: According to Levy County Sheriff's Office Lieutenant Scott Tummond, the Sheriff's Office was contacted by the U.S. Coast Guard to assist with the recovery of a white male that was found floating supine approximately thirty miles from the coast of Yankeetown, Florida.  The U.S. Coast Guard was notified by the Captain of a charter boat, which was fishing for grouper, who discovered the decedent.  It is unknown at this time who the decedent is or if there is a missing persons report.
